gnutls_x509_crt_set_flags(3)                                                                      gnutls                                                                      gnutls_x509_crt_set_flags(3)

NAME
       gnutls_x509_crt_set_flags - API function

SYNOPSIS
       #include <gnutls/x509.h>

       void gnutls_x509_crt_set_flags(gnutls_x509_crt_t cert, unsigned int flags);

ARGUMENTS
       gnutls_x509_crt_t cert
                   A type gnutls_x509_crt_t

       unsigned int flags
                   flags from the gnutls_x509_crt_flags

DESCRIPTION
       This  function  will  set flags for the specified certificate.  Currently this is useful for the GNUTLS_X509_CRT_FLAG_IGNORE_SANITY which allows importing certificates even if they have known is‐
       sues.

SINCE
       3.6.0

REPORTING BUGS
       Report bugs to <bugs@gnutls.org>.
       Home page: https://www.gnutls.org

